\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {6.2}{\ignorespaces Control-loop latency ($\mu $s): PIVOT (parameter network invoked once, then lightweight dynamics rollout) vs.\ a direct approach (large network at every rollout step with 399-dim input). PIVOT rollouts operate on 17--1,717 parameters per step; direct rollouts propagate 357K--738K parameters per step. All values averaged over 5,000 JIT-compiled calls on an NVIDIA RTX A6000.}}{31}{table.caption.76}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:latency}{{6.2}{31}{Control-loop latency ($\mu $s): PIVOT (parameter network invoked once, then lightweight dynamics rollout) vs.\ a direct approach (large network at every rollout step with 399-dim input). PIVOT rollouts operate on 17--1,717 parameters per step; direct rollouts propagate 357K--738K parameters per step. All values averaged over 5,000 JIT-compiled calls on an NVIDIA RTX A6000}{table.caption.76}{}}
